body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, I'm Nicholas Wilson from CarQuest Automotive. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Joan Adams.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Joan! Could you please provide me with your contact number for our records?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my contact number is seven seven zero - two three four - five six eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Joan. And may I also have your email address for future correspondence?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Certainly, my email address is j.adams@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great! Thank you for sharing that information, Joan. Is there anything specific you are looking for at CarQuest Automotive today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling nervous about the inventory availability for the car model I'm interested in.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Joan. Let me check on that for you. Thank you for your patience.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Joan. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a wonderful day!
